1
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:15,400
I will give her
my own version of TLC.

2
00:00:15,467 --> 00:00:16,600
Mookie! Hey!

3
00:00:16,667 --> 00:00:17,100
Mookie!

4
00:00:17,167 --> 00:00:18,133
Ma'am!

5
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:18,967
Ma'am, something's
happening to Mookie!

6
00:00:19,033 --> 00:00:20,300
What was your dream about?

7
00:00:20,367 --> 00:00:23,533
Mookie's mother
is burying her alive.

8
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,700
Her seizure stopped
before 5 minutes had passed.

9
00:00:25,767 --> 00:00:27,933
I know I'm indebted to you.

10
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,533
But I'm sorry, I'll be blunt.
Stop being delusional.

11
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:34,967
It's been 17 years
since I last saw her.

12
00:00:35,067 --> 00:00:37,567
That was when we graduated
from medical school.

13
00:00:37,633 --> 00:00:39,733
Class of 2007.

14
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,533
My birth year.

15
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:42,600
Exactly.

16
00:00:42,667 --> 00:00:45,400
After three months,
I gave birth to you.

17
00:00:45,467 --> 00:00:47,867
My greatest achievement.

18
00:00:53,367 --> 00:00:54,467
You again?

19
00:01:30,433 --> 00:01:34,367
You're like a cockroach,
you never die!

20
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:37,833
And you drive
like you own the road!

21
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:40,167
Don't be dumb.

22
00:01:40,233 --> 00:01:41,500
I'm not dumb.

23
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:43,067
If I acted foolishly,

24
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:45,000
that was me
being a victim to you!

25
00:01:45,067 --> 00:01:50,133
Just admit that
you're playing the victim.

26
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:52,900
Your daughter
took the side of the person

27
00:01:52,967 --> 00:01:55,267
you claim to have
a victim mentality.

28
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:57,767
Didn't you drop the charges

29
00:01:57,833 --> 00:02:00,867
because your daughter
told you so? For my sake.

30
00:02:00,933 --> 00:02:02,933
You know, you are delusional.

31
00:02:03,767 --> 00:02:04,800
Who do you think you are?

32
00:02:05,767 --> 00:02:09,333
I cared for and raised
Mookie for 17 years.

33
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:12,533
And here you are,
coming into our lives,

34
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:14,567
wearing a cheap, preloved blouse

35
00:02:14,667 --> 00:02:18,033
and ruining my relationship
with my daughter.

36
00:02:18,100 --> 00:02:21,667
I care for Mookie.
And I know you're hurting her.

37
00:02:21,733 --> 00:02:23,267
Really?

38
00:02:23,333 --> 00:02:24,433
Where's your proof?

39
00:02:25,633 --> 00:02:28,200
Can you prove your accusations?

40
00:02:29,933 --> 00:02:31,767
Hi, Mookie.

41
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:33,633
- Auntie Astrid.
- Hello, hello.

42
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:34,700
Hello.

43
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:40,300
Mommy's not here.

44
00:02:40,367 --> 00:02:43,067
But how are you, Auntie?

45
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:44,900
I'm okay.

46
00:02:44,967 --> 00:02:47,000
Do you want me to help you?

47
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:49,367
- No, I can manage.
- Are you sure?

48
00:02:49,433 --> 00:02:50,967
There.

49
00:02:51,033 --> 00:02:52,033
I'll assist you.

50
00:02:52,100 --> 00:02:53,300
Thank you, Auntie.

51
00:02:53,367 --> 00:02:56,633
I should ask you instead.

52
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:58,500
How are you feeling?

53
00:02:58,567 --> 00:03:01,267
We felt scared
when you had a seizure.

54
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:03,067
I'm okay, Auntie.

55
00:03:03,933 --> 00:03:05,167
That's good.

56
00:03:05,233 --> 00:03:06,900
Is Flor inside?

57
00:03:06,967 --> 00:03:09,700
I left my ring
in the powder room.

58
00:03:09,767 --> 00:03:11,767
Good thing she saw it.
I'll be right back.

59
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:12,833
Flor?

60
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:15,233
- Flor?
- Auntie?

61
00:03:18,233 --> 00:03:21,633
Can I ask you a question?

62
00:03:21,733 --> 00:03:23,567
Sure. What is it, Mookie?

63
00:03:25,367 --> 00:03:30,100
I just remembered something,
when I was 5 years old.

64
00:03:32,100 --> 00:03:36,100
There was a man
who often held a teddy bear.

65
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:40,233
I'm thinking,
maybe you know him?

66
00:03:42,033 --> 00:03:46,067
Oh, that was
Doctor Charles Marfori.

67
00:03:46,133 --> 00:03:49,367
That's his trademark.
Teddy bear and lollipop.

68
00:03:49,433 --> 00:03:50,967
Good thing
you still remember that.

69
00:03:52,467 --> 00:03:53,600
Yes.

70
00:03:58,133 --> 00:04:02,133
The problem with you
is you're such a know-it-all.

71
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:04,100
You do more than what people
expect from you.

72
00:04:04,167 --> 00:04:07,167
You play weaker
than my daughter.

73
00:04:07,233 --> 00:04:08,867
Wait for your karma.

74
00:04:08,933 --> 00:04:11,333
You'll end up in jail

75
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,933
once your daughter reports you
to the DSWD.

76
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,167
How dare you?

77
00:04:15,233 --> 00:04:17,567
You're not even a mother.

78
00:04:17,633 --> 00:04:19,433
What do you know?

79
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,533
I treat Mookie as a daughter.

80
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:24,933
She's not your dead child!

81
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,800
Don't drag my child into this!

82
00:04:26,867 --> 00:04:28,967
But you can interfere
with my child's life?

83
00:04:30,067 --> 00:04:35,033
You know, your daughter is lucky
that she didn't meet her mother.

84
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:36,367
Darn you!

85
00:04:36,433 --> 00:04:37,800
How dare you?

86
00:04:37,867 --> 00:04:39,100
Ouch! Ouch!

87
00:04:39,167 --> 00:04:41,333
What? Leave my daughter
out of this!

88
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:42,300
You're a beast!

89
00:04:42,367 --> 00:04:43,667
You're worse than a beast!

90
00:04:55,267 --> 00:04:56,600
My face!

91
00:04:56,667 --> 00:05:00,567
I'll pour boiling caramelized
sugar on your face next time!

92
00:05:02,867 --> 00:05:04,967
Stop recording!

93
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:11,433
You know, I shouldn't have
dropped the charges against you.

94
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:14,033
Because you should rot in jail!

95
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,133
You go first!

96
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,700
Dr. Marfori's office.

97
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:40,700
Hello?

98
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:46,667
Is this
Dr. Charles Marfori's office?

99
00:05:46,733 --> 00:05:48,567
May I know who's calling?

100
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:51,500
This is Maria Angela Caparas.

101
00:05:51,567 --> 00:05:53,100
Please hold the line.

102
00:05:53,167 --> 00:05:54,633
You have a phone call, Doctor.

103
00:05:57,367 --> 00:05:59,700
Mookie? Is that you?

104
00:05:59,767 --> 00:06:01,833
Yes, this is Mookie.

105
00:06:03,900 --> 00:06:06,200
How did you know me?

106
00:06:06,267 --> 00:06:08,600
I was your pediatrician
when you were a child.

107
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:10,200
I remember you.

108
00:06:10,267 --> 00:06:12,867
You and my daughter
have the same name.

109
00:06:12,933 --> 00:06:14,033
How are you?

110
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:15,833
It's been a long time.

111
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:19,167
I'm still sick.

112
00:06:19,233 --> 00:06:20,867
How may I help you, Mookie?

113
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:25,233
I just wanted to know...

114
00:06:25,967 --> 00:06:29,100
Doc, weren't you my pediatrician
back then?

115
00:06:29,167 --> 00:06:35,200
I only wanted to know my
illnesses since I was a child?

116
00:06:35,267 --> 00:06:38,433
Wait. I'm confused.

117
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:41,200
Do you have a serious
medical condition now, Mookie?

118
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:43,067
Is that what you're telling me?

119
00:06:43,133 --> 00:06:44,800
Yes.

120
00:06:44,867 --> 00:06:50,033
Didn't I have plenty of medical
conditions since I was born?

121
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:53,800
Like autoimmune diseases.

122
00:06:53,867 --> 00:06:57,333
And I have leukemia, right?

123
00:06:57,400 --> 00:07:00,967
No, you never had leukemia.

124
00:07:01,033 --> 00:07:04,067
In fact,
you were in perfect health.

125
00:07:04,133 --> 00:07:04,933
What?

126
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,933
You weren't sick when
you were a child, Mookie.

127
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:16,100
But that's impossible.

128
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:18,600
I've been sick all my life.

129
00:07:18,667 --> 00:07:19,800
I was your pediatrician

130
00:07:19,867 --> 00:07:22,900
from three to four months old
until 5 years old.

131
00:07:22,967 --> 00:07:26,500
I'm telling you, you don't have
a serious medical condition.

132
00:07:26,567 --> 00:07:31,600
You had the usual coughs and
colds, but that's just about it.

133
00:07:31,667 --> 00:07:35,333
Sorry, but are you sure
you remember me?

134
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:38,867
Didn't you mistake me
for another patient?

135
00:07:38,933 --> 00:07:40,733
With a name like Mookie?

136
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:44,367
You and my daughter have
the same name, Maria Angela.

137
00:07:44,433 --> 00:07:46,833
Olivia is your mom, right?

138
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,100
Yes.

139
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:52,400
I remember she requested
for all your medical records.

140
00:07:52,467 --> 00:07:55,133
I never saw her again
after that day.

141
00:07:58,333 --> 00:08:00,867
If I was healthy
since I was a child...

142
00:08:02,867 --> 00:08:05,900
what are those medicines
that my mom is giving me?

143
00:08:24,133 --> 00:08:27,300
Why did you fight back
against your employer?

144
00:08:27,367 --> 00:08:30,067
She said things
about Baby Kayla.

145
00:08:30,133 --> 00:08:33,733
She's crazy.
Why did she involve our child?

146
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:36,000
You did the right thing.

147
00:08:36,067 --> 00:08:39,067
She deserves to get hit
just even once.

148
00:08:39,133 --> 00:08:43,600
I'm just worried that
she'll come back for you.

149
00:08:43,667 --> 00:08:45,900
I don't think she'll do that.

150
00:08:45,967 --> 00:08:48,400
She knows Mookie
didn't report her

151
00:08:48,467 --> 00:08:51,433
in return for dropping
the charges against me.

152
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,767
And she's scared to lose Mookie.

153
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:56,100
I'm sure she'll leave me alone.

154
00:09:51,967 --> 00:09:52,933
Dan.

155
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:53,767
- Hey, Emma.
- Here.
Drink some water first.

156
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:57,200
Thank you.

157
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:04,100
Tomorrow is August 5.

158
00:10:07,567 --> 00:10:09,733
Oh, yes.

159
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:15,500
It's been 17 years
since the landslide happened.

160
00:10:17,433 --> 00:10:20,400
Kayla would've celebrated
her 18th birthday soon.

161
00:10:20,467 --> 00:10:23,900
We haven't visited her
since we moved here.

162
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:27,500
Emma, what for?

163
00:10:30,067 --> 00:10:33,233
I know Kayla
doesn't have a grave.

164
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:36,200
But I want to light
a candle for her.

165
00:10:39,233 --> 00:10:41,000
Sure, if that's what you want.

166
00:10:42,533 --> 00:10:47,900
It seems important to you to
go there on the day Kayla died.

167
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:50,633
We're going.

168
00:10:52,533 --> 00:10:55,367
I grieved for 17 years.

169
00:10:55,433 --> 00:10:58,933
It's time to bury the memories.

170
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:02,933
So I can be free from the past.

171
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:07,667
So that I won't have to look
for Kayla in other children.

172
00:11:08,767 --> 00:11:11,200
Maybe if I can say
goodbye to her,

173
00:11:11,267 --> 00:11:13,533
I'll forget about Mookie, too.

174
00:11:45,433 --> 00:11:47,433
Who does she think she is?

175
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:13,967
Hello?

176
00:12:15,867 --> 00:12:16,967
Yes, Jennifer?

177
00:12:18,033 --> 00:12:20,267
Why are you calling
instead of Astrid?

178
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:23,233
Hold on, hold on.

179
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:25,267
The reception here is bad.

180
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:26,367
I'll call you back.

181
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:55,967
Why does the internet
have to be down now?

182
00:13:05,733 --> 00:13:07,900
I need to go
to the office today.

183
00:13:07,967 --> 00:13:11,433
Your Aunt Astrid has been
acting strange lately.

184
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:12,900
But before I go...

185
00:13:13,867 --> 00:13:15,533
take your medicine.

186
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,833
That's my girl.

187
00:13:29,567 --> 00:13:32,800
So, Flor is downstairs.

188
00:13:32,867 --> 00:13:36,000
If you need anything,
just tell her to call me.

189
00:13:36,067 --> 00:13:37,367
I'll come home right away.

190
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:40,800
Bye.

191
00:14:06,267 --> 00:14:08,867
The nerve of that woman!

192
00:14:08,933 --> 00:14:12,467
I'll see to it that she'll
never see Mookie ever again.

193
00:14:16,467 --> 00:14:17,933
Hello?

194
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,333
Are you listening?

195
00:14:21,967 --> 00:14:22,633
Yes.

196
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:27,833
Why do you sound reluctant?

197
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:33,067
You know what?

198
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,300
Since Mookie had a seizure...

199
00:14:38,733 --> 00:14:41,267
I've noticed that
you're acting strangely.

200
00:14:43,233 --> 00:14:44,767
What is it, Astrid?

201
00:14:47,767 --> 00:14:49,833
Why don't you get
straight to the point?

202
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:53,000
Do you think I'm a monster?

203
00:14:54,233 --> 00:14:56,133
That I'm a horrible mother?

204
00:14:57,033 --> 00:14:59,033
Is that what you think of me?

205
00:15:00,367 --> 00:15:02,167
Of course not.

206
00:15:02,267 --> 00:15:04,133
Of course not, Olive.

207
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:06,500
What do I know? Right?

208
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:07,900
I don't have a child.

209
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:13,733
And I have no right
to judge you as a mother.

210
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:19,667
Mookie is the only person
who has the right to do that.

211
00:15:29,333 --> 00:15:30,967
Mookie, I have to go.

212
00:15:31,033 --> 00:15:31,800
Bye.

213
00:15:33,533 --> 00:15:34,567
Be safe.

214
00:15:51,433 --> 00:15:52,700
Bye, Ma'am.

215
00:15:58,700 --> 00:15:59,800
Flor!

216
00:15:59,867 --> 00:16:00,600
Yes?

217
00:16:00,667 --> 00:16:03,367
Can you close the gate later?

218
00:16:03,433 --> 00:16:04,300
Why?

219
00:16:04,367 --> 00:16:06,300
I want to catch some fresh air.

220
00:16:06,367 --> 00:16:08,067
Oh, you want to catch
some fresh air.

221
00:16:08,167 --> 00:16:11,800
Okay. But stay inside.
Don't go anywhere.

222
00:16:12,733 --> 00:16:14,800
I'll just check
what I'm cooking.

223
00:16:14,867 --> 00:16:15,700
Okay, Flor.

224
00:16:15,767 --> 00:16:17,633
- Thank you.
- I'll be right back.

225
00:16:17,700 --> 00:16:18,567
Stay here.

226
00:16:37,067 --> 00:16:38,100
Zayn!

227
00:16:39,467 --> 00:16:40,367
Hey, Mookie!

228
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:42,133
Zayn!

229
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:46,267
Zayn.

230
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:47,900
How are you?

231
00:16:47,967 --> 00:16:48,733
I'm okay.

232
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:51,933
But can I ask you a favor?

233
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,667
Sure. What is it?

234
00:16:57,767 --> 00:17:00,667
Can you search
what medicine this is?

235
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:03,033
Sure. Wait.

236
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:09,500
There.

237
00:17:20,233 --> 00:17:20,800
My...

238
00:17:21,733 --> 00:17:22,867
oh my gosh!

239
00:17:25,733 --> 00:17:26,800
Mookie, why?

240
00:17:26,867 --> 00:17:27,867
What's the problem?

241
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:29,867
The...

242
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:38,333
The Canixidol my mom
is giving me is for animals.

243
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:39,167
What?

244
00:17:39,233 --> 00:17:40,933
Are you sure? Let me see.

245
00:17:41,867 --> 00:17:43,067
Read it carefully.

246
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:47,333
It says...

247
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:51,300
it's a muscle relaxant
for animals.

248
00:17:51,367 --> 00:17:52,933
But when you administer it
to a person,

249
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,133
he can get paralyzed.

250
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:58,400
You mean you couldn't walk
before because of that?

251
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:00,867
Exactly.

252
00:18:02,100 --> 00:18:05,967
I felt better when my mom
didn't give me that.

253
00:18:06,033 --> 00:18:07,900
I can walk.

254
00:18:07,967 --> 00:18:09,367
Look at me now, right?

255
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,033
But why?

256
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:13,400
I don't get it.

257
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:15,167
Why would she give it to you?

258
00:18:15,233 --> 00:18:16,567
It doesn't make sense.

259
00:18:17,833 --> 00:18:22,233
My medical records
are kept in my mom's room.

260
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:23,700
I need to see them.

261
00:18:24,733 --> 00:18:26,967
I need to know the truth, Zayn.

262
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,900
I learned this
from a video on YT.

263
00:18:42,833 --> 00:18:45,333
Come on! Come on!

264
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:47,233
Come on!

265
00:18:50,333 --> 00:18:51,400
Success!

266
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,900
Let's go!

267
00:18:56,967 --> 00:18:57,767
Zayn?

268
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:04,633
Maybe it's much better
if you go home for now.

269
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:08,900
My mom might catch you here.

270
00:19:08,967 --> 00:19:10,467
I don't want you
to get in trouble.

271
00:19:11,733 --> 00:19:12,567
Are you sure?

272
00:19:16,133 --> 00:19:16,867
Okay.

273
00:19:18,133 --> 00:19:20,200
But be careful, Mookie. Okay?

274
00:19:20,267 --> 00:19:22,533
Promise me you'll be careful.

275
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:26,767
I will.
Okay.

276
00:19:27,767 --> 00:19:28,600
Go ahead.

277
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:24,267
Hello?

278
00:20:25,167 --> 00:20:26,700
Olivia Caparas?

279
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:27,733
Yes?

280
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:29,433
Who's this?

281
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:31,700
Charles Marfori.

282
00:20:31,767 --> 00:20:33,000
Dr. Charles?

283
00:20:34,033 --> 00:20:35,167
This is Dr. Charles.

284
00:20:36,667 --> 00:20:38,533
How did you get my number?

285
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:42,933
I don't usually get numbers if
not directly from that person.

286
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,667
But I'm really bothered.

287
00:20:44,733 --> 00:20:47,000
So I asked and looked
for your number.

288
00:20:47,067 --> 00:20:49,333
Your daughter called me
yesterday and...

289
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:51,500
That's impossible, Doctor.

290
00:20:51,567 --> 00:20:54,500
I'm sure it wasn't a prank call.

291
00:20:54,567 --> 00:20:56,400
I talked to Mookie yesterday.

292
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:58,500
My daughter doesn't know you.

293
00:20:58,567 --> 00:21:01,433
Apparently, she does.

294
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:04,667
And she was actually asking
about her medical history.

295
00:21:05,533 --> 00:21:07,033
I'm sorry, Doc. I have to go.

296
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:12,867
Obet, go back to the house
right now.

297
00:21:12,933 --> 00:21:13,867
Hurry!

298
00:21:24,633 --> 00:21:25,767
I was your pediatrician

299
00:21:25,833 --> 00:21:28,833
from three to four months old
until 5 years old.

300
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:32,900
I'm telling you, you don't have
a serious medical condition.

301
00:21:32,967 --> 00:21:35,900
Dr. Charles was right.
I was healthy when I was a kid.

302
00:21:35,967 --> 00:21:37,600
I don't have any illnesses.

303
00:21:37,667 --> 00:21:39,533
You look familiar.

304
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:40,333
I'm Bukoy.

305
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:41,533
Yes. Bukoy.

306
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,033
How's your baby?

307
00:21:43,133 --> 00:21:44,267
I bet she's all grown up.

308
00:21:44,333 --> 00:21:45,367
She's gone, Bukoy.

309
00:21:45,433 --> 00:21:47,333
Our child has been dead
for 17 years now.

310
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:49,567
She was buried alive
during the landslide.

311
00:21:49,633 --> 00:21:51,033
That's impossible.

312
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:52,200
I saw her that day.

313
00:21:52,267 --> 00:21:54,767
I'm sure,
a woman was carrying her.

314
00:21:54,833 --> 00:21:55,733
Are you sure?

315
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:57,867
Do you know her?
Do you know the woman?

316
00:21:57,933 --> 00:21:59,100
Mookie, what are...

317
00:22:01,033 --> 00:22:04,233
I will only ask you once, Mommy.

318
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:06,800
Am I really sick?

319
00:22:08,467 --> 00:22:10,033
Baby Kayla is alive.
